    "Relatively large number (27.8%) expect bad outcomes, and within that, 14% expect catastrophic impact.",
    "It is interesting to note that respondents from tech AI groups are more optimistic than the respondents approaching AI issues from the theoretical point of view, most notably in expecting good long-term outcomes after achieving superintelligence (60.5% vs. 47.0%) and fearing much less catastrophic outcomes (7% vs. 14%).Table 1: Attitudes towards the impact of Generative AI on humanity (survey results) AI groups Theory Tech Total Good outcomes 47.0 60.5 53.8 Neutral 17.5 19.5 18.5 Bad outcomes 35.5 20.0 27.8 in which catastrophic 21.0 7.0 14.0 Total 100.0 100.0 100.0 Source: Muller and Bostrom [42] and own calculationsNordhaus [45] was intrigued by the same question and conducted elaborate tests with inconclusive results.AI singularity is a hypothetical idea where artificial intelligence becomes smarter than people (reaches a level of superintelligence which humans cannot achieve) and continues to improve and develop technology exponentially.",
